    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="443"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d443">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.20/561</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Harry A. McBride</persName>, Special
                        Representative of President <persName>Roosevelt</persName> in Liberia, to
                        the President of Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Barclay</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-21">March 21,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. President</hi>: In our recent conversation I
                    had the honor of informing you that in order to safeguard the health of United
                    States troops, the United States War Department requested the cooperation of the
                    Liberian health officials in a manner similar to that existing in the United
                    States between the Army authorities and the local Federal and State
                    agencies.</p>
                <p>The War Department requested that American Army medical authorities be given
                    health and sanitary control in all strictly defense areas which may be set-up
                    under our agreement, as well as in any contiguous areas which such medical
                    authorities might deem to present a health hazard to the United States troops.
                    It was my understanding that you are willing to grant these facilities in the
                    plans now being made for the defense and protection of the Republic.</p>
                <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harry</hi> A. <hi rend="smallcaps">McBride</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
